- 2.0.2 | Feb 20 2026:

[Change] ipset batch loading via ipset restore; replaces per-entry $IPSET add
      loop (31K+ fork+exec calls) with single awk pre-filter piped to
      ipset restore -exist, reducing load time from minutes to seconds
      (functions.apf)
[Change] ipset_load() and ipset_update() now log per-set "loading/updating
      set $name from $source" before processing begins, providing visibility
      into which set is being loaded during long ipset operations
      (functions.apf)
